    "department": "Applied AI",
    "description": "ABOUT THE ROLE\n\nWe’re looking for an experienced Engineering Manager to found and lead the ChatGPT Infrastructure team in London.\n\nYou’ll lead a small, talent-dense, high-impact team building the core runtime primitives and infrastructure that underpin how new ChatGPT experiences are built and scaled.\n\nThis is a high-ownership, 0→1 leadership role blending hands-on technical leadership, startup-style problem solving, and founding-team building.\n\nYou’ll operate with a high degree of autonomy, working closely with product and research teams to design and build critical, load-bearing infrastructure components, while establishing the engineering culture and high-trust environment that will come to define our London presence.\n\n\nYOU WILL\n\n - Build and lead a small, talent-dense team responsible for foundational runtime systems powering ChatGPT.\n\n - Drive the development of core infrastructure primitives that product engineers rely on to build new ChatGPT experiences (e.g., runtime frameworks, service integration patterns, and extensibility mechanisms within the ChatGPT runtime).\n\n - Define and evolve the technical architecture of the ChatGPT runtime, unlocking new feature capabilities as part of our next phase of rapid growth.\n\n - Work closely with product and research teams to ensure infrastructure enables rapid product development while maintaining strong reliability and operational discipline.\n\n - Own the reliability of the systems your team builds—participating in incident response, supporting deployments, and helping evolve our operational model toward a follow-the-sun global infrastructure team.\n\n - Hire and develop the early London team, helping establish the technical bar, culture, and operating model that will define our London engineering presence.\n\n - Serve as a technical leader and connector between the London office and the broader global ChatGPT infrastructure organization.\n   \n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n - 7+ years of hands-on software engineering experience, ideally building large-scale distributed systems, developer platforms, or infrastructure products.\n\n - Experience building and leading high-caliber engineering teams, particularly in startup or early-stage initiatives within larger companies.\n\n - Proven ability to create a high-trust, high-agency culture where strong engineers can move quickly, take ownership, and operate effectively in ambiguous environments.\n\n - Strong judgment in hiring and talent development, with a track record of building small, high-performing teams and maintaining a high technical bar.\n\n - Track record of remaining deeply technical as a leader, contributing to architecture and design decisions while enabling others to do their best work.\n\n - Experience operating in 0→1 or high-ambiguity environments, where teams are defining problems and building systems from scratch.\n\n - Experience running production systems in cloud environments (e.g., AWS, GCP, Azure).\n\n - Based in or willing to relocate to London.\n\nAbout OpenAI\n\nOpenAI is an AI research and deployment company dedicated to ensuring that general-purpose artificial intelligence benefits all of humanity. We push the boundaries of the capabilities of AI systems and seek to safely deploy them to the world through our products. AI is an extremely powerful tool that must be created with safety and human needs at its core, and to achieve our mission, we must encompass and value the many different perspectives, voices, and experiences that form the full spectrum of humanity. \n\nWe are an equal opportunity employer, and we do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, age, veteran status, disability, genetic information, or other applicable legally protected characteristic.\n\nFor additional information, please see OpenAI’s Affirmative Action and Equal Employment Opportunity Policy Statement https://cdn.openai.com/policies/eeo-policy-statement.pdf.\n\nBackground checks for applicants will be administered in accordance with applicable law, and qualified applicants with arrest or conviction records will be considered for employment consistent with those laws, including the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, the Los Angeles County Fair Chance Ordinance for Employers, and the California Fair Chance Act, for US-based candidates. For unincorporated Los Angeles County workers: we reasonably believe that criminal history may have a direct, adverse and negative relationship with the following job duties, potentially resulting in the withdrawal of a conditional offer of employment: protect computer hardware entrusted to you from theft, loss or damage; return all computer hardware in your possession (including the data contained therein) upon termination of employment or end of assignment; and maintain the confidentiality of proprietary, confidential, and non-public information. In addition, job duties require access to secure and protected information technology systems and related data security obligations.\n\nTo notify OpenAI that you believe this job posting is non-compliant, please submit a report through this form https://form.asana.com/?d=57018692298241\u0026k=5MqR40fZd7jlxVUh5J-UeA. No response will be provided to inquiries unrelated to job posting compliance.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities, and requests can be made via this link https://form.asana.com/?k=bQ7w9h3iexRlicUdWRiwvg\u0026d=57018692298241.\n\nOpenAI Global Applicant Privacy Policy https://cdn.openai.com/policies/global-employee-and-contractor-privacy-policy.pdf\n\nAt OpenAI, we believe artificial intelligence has the potential to help people solve immense global challenges, and we want the upside of AI to be widely shared. Join us in shaping the future of technology.",
